caption: The quality has definitely gone down the past few months. I mean for $3 a roll, you don't expect fine dining, but I used to come here often as it's close by, affordable, and decent quality. But it's quickly become hit or miss in terms of quality and timeliness. The rice, a crucial part of sushi, has come out way too mushy or too much rice vinegar, making the overall experience quite sour, no pun intended. Would recommend alloting 1 hr+ before you expect to pick up your order on peak hours. Can't speak on delivery. Good luck to y'all

I asked the woman on the phone about how long my food was sitting out while it was waiting for the driver but she didn’t give me a straight answer, just told me that they were busy. Apparently my order was picked up with two other orders so mine was likely dropped off last (not the restaurant’s fault). She apologized for the inconvenience which I appreciated but my food was definitely in bad shape by the time it got to me, had clearly sat out for a while. TL;DR mistakes, poor service, and long waits!  I have ordered from here quite a lot but was frustrated with a recent poor experience. First, they lost my online takeout order, then had me pay for a wrong order. I was going to call it quits and just take the wrong order, but they’d given the food away to other tables.  I then placed another order just so I could have anything for dinner, and they made me wait AN HOUR while they made my food. I ended up waiting for 1.5 hrs entirely due to their mistakes and understaffing! At the very least I would’ve expected to be the top of the queue to get my food, if not outright refunded.  It was Valentine’s Day and I know they were very busy, but I was extremely disappointed. The manager called after I contacted the owner, and only offered 50% off a future order and little sympathy for the inconvenience. Normally I wouldn’t complain publicly, but it was such a bad experience and sadly I do not expect to be back any time soon.
